canonical:
  title: 永嘉鄕校諸仙設宴送行作詩爲謝
  author: 李瑱
  language: lzh
  text: 槐市諸儒敞別筵畫堂銀燭夜如年杯盤錯落眞非分絃管鏘洋最可憐座上三行相玉暎樽前七字幾珠聯飮狂解倒蟬塲客舞巧誰呼鶴背仙坐撫敢言嘉政化挽留休唱好因緣寒生厚意誠難負傾盡囊儲到一錢
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 永嘉鄕校諸仙設宴送行作詩爲謝
  author: 李瑱
  language: lzh
  text: 槐市諸儒敞別筵。畫堂銀燭夜如年。杯盤錯落眞非分。絃管鏘洋最可憐。座上三行相玉暎。樽前七字幾珠聯。飮狂解倒蟬塲客。舞巧誰呼鶴背仙。坐撫敢言嘉政化。挽留休唱好因緣。寒生厚意誠難負。傾盡囊儲到一錢。
korean:
  title: 영가 향교 제생들이 차려주는 송별연에 시로 사례하며
  author: 이진
  language: kor
  text: |-
    괴시의 여러 선비들 송별연을 차렸는데
    화당 은촉에 밤이 길어 해와 같네
    풍성한 배반이 분수에 넘치나
    닐리리 현관 소리 마음에 흐뭇하네
    좌상의 석 줄 손은 옥처럼 맞 비치고
    술잔 앞의 일곱 자 시는 몇 구슬을 꿰었는고
    무턱대고 마시니 곤드레된 선장객
    덩실덩실 추는 춤에 여봐라 학배선아
    앉아서 다스렸으니 무슨 선정 있었던고
    굳이 만류하느라고 좋은 인연 노래 마소
    빈한한 서생들의 후의를 못 저버려
    주머니 돈 다 털어 냈네 일전 아직 남았구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0210_010_0250&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 영가(永嘉) : '
    value: 안동(安東)의 옛 이름.
  - key: '[주-D002] 괴시(槐市) : '
    value: 주대(周代) 성동(城東) 7리에 괴목(槐木) 수백 줄을 심어 수도(隧道)를 만들고 제생(諸生)들이 초하루ㆍ보름에 모여 물산(物産)ㆍ경전(經傳)ㆍ악기(樂器)들을 팔고 사기도 하며 괴목 아래에서 글을 토론했다. 《三輔黃圖》
english:
  title: A Poem of Thanks for the Farewell Banquet Given by the Scholars of Yongga County School
  author: Lee Jin
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Beneath the scholar's market, a grand farewell feast is laid,
    In painted halls with silver candles, night stretches like a year.
    Course upon course overflows what measure could contain—
    The strings and pipes ring out so sweetly, stirring joy within.

    Three rows of hands at table gleam like jade reflecting jade,
    Before the wine cups, seven characters of verse link pearl to pearl.
    Intoxicated, the ship's captain tumbles without shame,
    And dancing lightly—who calls them a sage upon the crane's back?

    I sit in gratitude, yet what wisdom have I wrought?
    Do not insist on keeping me—spare the song of blessed fate.
    These humble scholars' kindness cuts too deep to turn away,
    I've emptied out my purse completely—not a coin remains.
  footnotes:
    - The 'scholar's market' (槐市) alludes to a legendary gathering place in Zhou Dynasty where scholars met beneath ancient locust trees to discuss learning and trade in wisdom.
    - The 'seven characters' refers to the composition of classical Chinese poetry, suggesting the other scholars have composed verse for this occasion.
    - The 'sage upon the crane's back' is a Daoist immortal image, used here playfully to describe the dancers.
    - The final couplet expresses both gratitude and self-deprecation—the poet has given all he has despite his meager means, emphasizing the genuine warmth of the farewell.
